OL,3,C'It was a frightening time': Ex-miners
OL,4,Chaunted by memories of Orgreave
OL,6,FOpinion remains divided about who
OL,7,Facted first, but violence erupted on
OL,8,Fboth sides.
OL,10,FKevin said he became an unwitting
OL,11,Faccomplice to the overreaction of
OL,12,Fpolice.
OL,14,F"The police stopped me and said, 'will
OL,15,Fyou give us a hand to move these
OL,16,Fstones - there's ambulances waiting to
OL,17,Fcome down, with pickets in'," he said.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/13
