OL,3,C'It was a frightening time': Ex-miners
OL,4,Chaunted by memories of Orgreave
OL,6,F"So reluctantly me and a couple more
OL,7,Flad, threw these stones to one side.
OL,8,FThe ambulances never came - police and
OL,9,Fthe horses came and chased us back
OL,10,Fdown the field."
OL,12,FThe mounted police forced the miners
OL,13,Fup a field as stones and missiles were
OL,14,Fthrown. Ninety-five miners were
OL,15,Farrested.
OL,17,FMore than 100 people on both sides
OL,18,Fwere injured.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/13
