OL,3,C'It was a frightening time': Ex-miners
OL,4,Chaunted by memories of Orgreave
OL,6,F"The line that gets me every time is
OL,7,Fwhen they march back to work after a
OL,8,Fyear, there is no deal, and one of the
OL,9,Fguys says 'I stuck my chest out and
OL,10,Fheld my head high, but I was dead
OL,11,Finside.' It just gets me every time."
OL,13,FGordon Bird, who ran a newsagent in
OL,14,Fthe area, said Orgreave changed the
OL,15,Frelationship between police and the
OL,16,Fminers, in some cases irreversibly.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/13
