OL,3,C'It was a frightening time': Ex-miners
OL,4,Chaunted by memories of Orgreave
OL,6,FHe said: "In my shop (before the
OL,7,FBattle of Orgreave) we arranged to
OL,8,Fhave a raffle and the prize was a
OL,9,Fchicken and all the vegetables -
OL,10,Fenough to feed a family of four - and
OL,11,Fthe police in particular put theirs
OL,12,Fback and also put some more prizes in,
OL,13,Fso that more miners got their
OL,14,FChristmas dinner.
OL,16,F"What took place on that picket line -
OL,17,Fsome people will never like the
OL,18,Fpolice, whatever they do, because of
OL,19,Fwhat went on that day."
